          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "DPSG Vasundhara - Sector 9,Vasundhara"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Snigdha Goel"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-05-19",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Hey everyone! I am sure you all must be seeing very good reviews about this school as you are scrolling. But please do not go by the reviews written here. These are all written by the teachers and faculties of this school.\n\nI myself was a student studying in this school till class 10th and here is the honest review:\n• The school focuses on more activities rather than studying.\n\n• They have divided the class into groups and ask the children to peer educate each other. The children are not able to understand the topics this way. If children have to study on their own, then what is the role of teachers??!!\n\n• The school felicitates the students in a very improper way or doesn't felicitate at all. In the name of the scholar ward, they just provide certificates and no trophy or badge.\n\n• The staff and teachers do not listen to the concerns and solve the issues of parents and students.\n\n• Every new financial year, the school raises it's fee but the quality of education and services is declining every year.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "DPSG Vasundhara - Sector 9,Vasundhara"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Swati Goel"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-05-19",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "The school used to be good at some point of time but not now, except studies they focus on all things which are not very much required.\n1No focus on studies at all.\n\n2 Every year they hike the fees. This year hike of 16000 annually.\n\n3 They charge for ACs but they are not functional. Students return from school drenched in sweat and irritated.\n\n4 inspite of increase in fees every year they keep cutting the cost, no almanac is given since so many years.\n\n5 This year, they gave only certificates to scholar students no trophies, no badges.\nThis is heights of cost cutting.\nMy daughter returned home very disappointed. She was scholar for 3 consecutive years, no blazer given.\nRidiculous\n\n6 they have stopped giving practice booklet, else they give some useless UI booklets.\n\n7 Anytime during the year, without giving prior information, they start taking the tests.\n\nI would suggest, not to get your ward admitted in DPS ghaziabad Vasundhara.\nThere are much better schools available",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
